description: The undefeated Gamecocks won their third NCAA title, and stole Iowa star Caitlin Clark's first and last chance at the ring.
title: South Carolina defeats Iowa to win the women's NCAA basketball championship

description: Israel withdraws troops from Khan Younis six months after the Hamas-led Oct. 7 attacks, as tens of thousands of Israelis hold anti-government protests.
title: Israel pulls some troops from southern Gaza, six months after Oct. 7 attacks

description: Consumers tend to spend about 10% more when they adopt mobile contactless payment methods, according to research from Assistant Professor Yuqian Xu at UNC-Chapel Hill.
title: Using your phone to pay is convenient, but it can also mean you spend more

description: NPR asked listeners to share what they're doing for the eclipse. Here are some memorable answers, from the new parents planning a themed baby shower to the mayor waving tourists off his small city.
title: How people across the U.S. are making the most of the solar eclipse

description: Rwandans are commemorating 30 years since the genocide in which an estimated 800,000 people were killed by government-backed extremists, shattering the small East African country.
title: Bill Clinton joins Rwandans in marking 30 years since their genocide

description: Some people feel he's too old. Others think there's a plan afoot to swap in a more popular Democrat. There's a swirl of reasons why some people don't accept that Biden will be on the ballot this year.
title: Yes, Biden is really running in November. But a lot of voters say they doubt it

description: President Biden and former President Donald Trump are still very close in polling on the 2024 presidential election. But below the surface, so key demographic groups appear to be shifting loyalty.

description: Friday's semifinal averaged 14.2 million viewers, making it the most-viewed women's basketball game on record and the largest audience for an ESPN basketball broadcast.
title: Iowa-UConn women's Final Four game is the most-watched hoops game in ESPN history
